Module com.example.demo

Class Addproduct

java.lang.Object
com.example.demo.Addproduct
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class Addproduct extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This class handles the Add Product form of the inventory management system. It allows the user to input details of a new product and add it to the inventory.

    • SearchBtn

      public void SearchBtn(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Handles the search button click event. Searches for parts by part ID or name and displays the search results in the associated parts table.
      Parameters:
      event - the event object

    • AddBtn

      public void AddBtn(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Handles the add button click event. Adds a selected part from the search results to the list of associated parts for the new product being added.
      Parameters:
      event - the event object

    • DeleteBtn

      public void DeleteBtn(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Handles the delete button click event. Deletes a selected associated part from the list of associated parts for the new product being added.
      Parameters:
      event - the event object

    • SaveClick

      public void SaveClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      This method is called when the save button is clicked. It retrieves data entered by the user, validates it, creates a new product object and saves it to the inventory. It also displays an error message if the data is invalid.
      Parameters:
      event - The event triggered by clicking the save button
      Throws:
      IOException - If there is an error while saving the product to the inventory

    • CancelClick

      public void CancelClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      This method is called when the cancel button is clicked. It goes back to the main screen of the inventory management system.
      Parameters:
      event - The event triggered by clicking the cancel button
      Throws:
      IOException - If there is an error while loading the main screen
